      "id": "bea63ff0-c1ee-4205-a346-692f2dfa7c79",
      "name": "Combine User & Heritage Data",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.merge",
      "typeVersion": 3.2,
      "position": [
        1152,
        496
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=Location: {{ $json.body.latitude }}, {{ $json.body.longitude }}\n\nUser Profile: {{ $('Get User Profile').item.json }}\n\nHeritage Data: {{ $('Fetch Heritage Data').item.json }}\n\nGenerate an immersive heritage narrative for this location.",
        "hasOutputParser": true,
        "options": {
          "systemMessage": "You are ChronoPath AI, a Digital Ancestor and heritage guide for Pune, India. Your role is to transform location data into immersive, personalized historical narratives.\n\nYou receive:\n- User profile (nationality, age, interests, language preference)\n- Current location coordinates\n- Heritage data from local APIs\n\nYour tasks:\n1. Analyze the heritage significance of the current location\n2. Adapt complex Indian history into relatable analogies for the user's nationality and background\n3. Create multi-sensory narratives that blend verified historical facts with living culture\n4. Explain WHY routes and paths were historically significant, not just WHAT happened\n5. Generate content in three formats: audio_script (conversational narration), visual_description (for image generation), and text_summary (brief key points)\n\nAdapt your tone and references based on user nationality. For European tourists, use European historical parallels. For American tourists, reference American history. Make the invisible history visible through storytelling.\n\nIf heritage data is unavailable or empty, use your knowledge of Pune's history and the location coordinates to provide a general historical context for the area. Acknowledge when specific heritage data is not available but still provide valuable historical insights."
        }
      },
      "id": "6646d5b3-49cd-4314-bb36-c35f6f8e9568",
      "name": "Heritage Guide Agent",
      "type": "@n8n/n8n-nodes-langchain.agent",
      "typeVersion": 3.1,
      "position": [
        1504,
        496
      ]
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
